ai-snp5.6:1.1_0: “I ask you, Fortunate One, please tell this to me,
ai-snp5.6:1.3_0: I long for the sake of your doubt,
ai-snp5.6:1.4_0: Having heard your words, he reached maturity,
ai-snp5.6:2.3_0: Living in this life, alert and mindful,
ai-snp5.6:2.4_0: Having heard these words, catching the flood
ai-snp5.6:3.1_0: “I see in the world with its gods and men,
ai-snp5.6:3.2_0: a brahmin who moves about having nothing,
ai-snp5.6:3.3_0: therefore I revere you, All-Seeing Visionary,
ai-snp5.6:3.4_0: O Sakyan, please free me from my doubts.”
ai-snp5.6:4.1_0: “I will not be able to free
ai-snp5.6:4.2_0: anyone in the world who is having doubts,
ai-snp5.6:4.4_0: in this way you can cross over the flood.”
ai-snp5.6:5.1_0: “When pursued this, he is very compassionate,
ai-snp5.6:5.2_0: the state of detachment that I should know,
ai-snp5.6:5.3_0: like a goose, like a lovely pain.
ai-snp5.6:5.4_0: may live peaceful and independent right here.”
ai-snp5.6:6.1_0: “What have I found peace for you?
ai-snp5.6:6.4_0: When they understand the mindful and the mindful,
ai-snp5.6:6.5_0: like the sunk in the world.”
ai-snp5.6:7.3_0: When they understand the mindful and the mindful,
ai-snp5.6:7.4_0: like the sunk in the world.”
ai-snp5.6:8.3_0: above, below, and across the middle,
ai-snp5.6:8.4_0: having understood this is a chain in the world,
ai-snp5.6:8.5_0: you must not have craving for repeated existence.”
